-- Kazakhstan Faces ‘Alarming’ Drought in Grain Areas, Kaztag Says
-- B y   S v e t l a n a   A n t o n c h e v a
-- 2012-07-17T16:59:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-17/kazakhstan-faces-alarming-drought-in-grain-areas-kaztag-says.html
Kazakhstan  faces an “alarming”
drought in grain growing regions, Kaztag reported, citing Deputy
Agriculture Minister Muslim Umiryayev.  Kazakhstan may export 10 million metric tons of grain this  
marketing year that started July 1, Umiryayev said, according
to the news service.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Svetlana Antoncheva in Astana, Kazakhstan at 
